@node "System" "System Requirements"

  To use dA cOOL pATCHER you need at least an Amiga (oh, can`t I use
  it on PeeZee ?) with harddisk and OS2.0. I heard that Da Cool Patcher
  runs on WinUAE too but you should use it on Amiga ;)

  dA cOOL pATCHER should be compatible up to A4000/060. It was successfully
  tested on A1200/030, A1200/040, A4000/040. I think there shouldn`t
  be any problems on higher machines. If there are, try to disable the
  caches, if my system patches are failing.  

  For the recommended installation of dA cOOL pATCHER you need the tool
  NewInstaller. Get it on Aminet (util/wb/NewInstaller.lha) or our homepage
  http://www.airsoft.home.pages.de.

  Additionally you must have the Workbench installed on your harddisk and
  boot with it.

@endnode

@node "history" "History"

  V1.0: (Internal Beta Version)

  - Gadtools Interface
  - patches files only
 
  
  V1.1: (Internal Beta Version)

  - Bugs fixed
  - patches disks too


  V1.2: (Shareware Release Version)

  - MUI Interface
  - alot of Bugs fixed
  - AmigaGuide® documentation
  - v1.2 is only quick recompile of my sources from December `97 


  Future plans:

  - more default patches
  - finish Patch editor

@endnode

@node "Cardware" "Shareware"

  This program is Shareware. If you like & use it @{"register" link "register"}  yourself by
  sending $15 (20DM) with the filled-in @{"Registration form" link "register"} to
  @{"this" link "autor"} adress. You`ll get a keyfile which enables the disabled options.
  So you have a lot more @{"features" link "option"}.

  Additionally I`m interested in errors or suggestions to dA cOOL pATCHER.
  Take a look @{"here" link "autor"}.    

  Please support programmers which are still developing for AMiGA!

@endnode

@node "why" "Why the hell shall I register?"

 The fullversion (=@{"keyfile" link "key"}) has some more really cool features:

 1. Use all default patches
 2. Create your own patches

 and more because of the future versions which run with the @{"keyfile" link "key"} undisabled,
 of course.

 @{"Register" link "register"} now.

@endnode

